.TH "pcie_bandwidth_capable" 9 "pcie_bandwidth_capable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pcie_bandwidth_capable \- calculate a PCI device's link bandwidth capability
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "u32" pcie_bandwidth_capable
.BI "(struct pci_dev *dev "  ","
.BI "enum pci_bus_speed *speed "  ","
.BI "enum pcie_link_width *width "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
PCI device
.IP "speed" 12
storage for link speed
.IP "width" 12
storage for link width
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calculate a PCI device's link bandwidth by querying for its link speed
and width, multiplying them, and applying encoding overhead.  The result
is in Mb/s, i.e., megabits/second of raw bandwidth.
